III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS

Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Seed Treatment & Planting -

Seeds require 400 to 500 kg of seeds or 400,000 tubers per hectare. Treat the seed before sowing in chemical and biological methods. In the chemical method, tubers are treated in 0.1 percent solution of VAWESTIN. By biological method, tubers are kept in cow urine and water (1:10) for 1 to 2 hours. Poths are made for sowing. The depth of the pit should be as much as the length of the seeds, planting the seeds in these pits and adding light soil.

Manure and fertilizer: -
Due to long periods of crop ripening, fertilizers and fertilizers are also high, therefore, 20 tons of dung / compost compost should be mixed uniformly before the last plowing of the farm, in addition to 300 kg of nitrogen (650 kg urea ), 85 kg Phosphorus (500 kg single super phosphate) and 60 kg Potash (100 kg Muratapaposh) should be used at a rate of hectare. Use full amount of phosphorus and potash during sowing and use the amount of nitrogen as following.
Autumn sugarcane: - Use the amount of Natarajan in the Sharadik sugarcane divided into four equal parts and use it in 30, 90, 120 and 150 days respectively.
Basant sugarcane: In the spring cane, use total amount of nitrogen divided into three equal parts and use it in 30, 90 and 120 days respectively.
        The use of nitrogen fertilizer increases with the use of nitrogen fertilizers in the application of nitrogen in powder and simultaneous protection from termites. 25 kg Zinc sulphate and 50 kg Ferrous sulphate should be used for sowing the zinc and iron micro-elements at the interval of 3 years as basis fertilizers.

Buds 5-7 cm Should be covered in deep depth and covered with mild soil. At the time of planting, keep the thin part of the buds above. At the time of sowing, the distance of buds from the buds is 8 cm. And the distance of the queues is 15 cm. Garlic planter can also be used for crop seeding in large areas.

1- Visit the field in which sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with hand and make a round pile by putting it on clean clothes. Remove the clay from finger to four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure until almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. Insert a notice sheet with a sample on which all the information is written, inside a plastic bag and outside a garment bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laborator
